towards everyone like you did.

00:16:59.352 --> 00:17:00.687 position:50% align:center
But, no.

00:17:00.770 --> 00:17:06.276 position:50% align:center
I actually wanted
to be number one.

00:17:06.359 --> 00:17:07.777 position:50% align:center
Talkative today, aren't we?

00:17:07.861 --> 00:17:10.905 position:50% align:center
Just answer me!

00:17:10.989 --> 00:17:14.909 position:50% align:center
What is the symbol
of peace, huh? Heh.

00:17:14.993 --> 00:17:16.244 position:50% align:center
That's tough.

00:17:16.327 --> 00:17:20.040 position:50% align:center
I'm not certain how
to explain it to you.

00:17:20.123 --> 00:17:22.042 position:50% align:center
I thought that this
country needed a hero

00:17:22.125 --> 00:17:24.127 position:50% align:center
who could inspire them,

00:17:24.210 --> 00:17:28.590 position:50% align:center
so I ran toward that
goal at full speed.

00:17:28.673 --> 00:17:31.301 position:50% align:center
I wanted to be a light
that was a beacon of hope,

00:17:31.384 --> 00:17:33.428 position:50% align:center
as well as a warning.

00:17:33.511 --> 00:17:35.221 position:50% align:center
I swore that that's
what I would become,

00:17:35.305 --> 00:17:38.391 position:50% align:center
and I never looked back.

00:17:38.475 --> 00:17:40.977 position:50% align:center
When you walked through
the streets back then,

00:17:41.061 --> 00:17:43.396 position:50% align:center
everyone was on edge.

00:17:43.480 --> 00:17:45.565 position:50% align:center
No matter how many
heroes there were,

00:17:45.648 --> 00:17:48.276 position:50% align:center
the crime rate never went down.

00:17:48.360 --> 00:17:53.615 position:50% align:center
Even more so than now,
everyone was afraid.

00:17:53.698 --> 00:17:56.326 position:50% align:center
I'm here because I want
to do something to help you!

00:17:56.409 --> 00:17:58.661 position:50% align:center
Please, All Might.

00:17:58.745 --> 00:18:00.580 position:50% align:center
[ALL MIGHT] I ignored
the kindness of the people

00:18:00.663 --> 00:18:03.249 position:50% align:center
around me and abandoned
those dear to me

00:18:03.333 --> 00:18:05.251 position:50% align:center
to walk this path.

00:18:05.335 --> 00:18:07.128 position:50% align:center
Maybe that was a mistake.

00:18:07.212 --> 00:18:08.797 position:50% align:center
[ENDEAVOR]
Your former sidekick.

00:18:08.880 --> 00:18:11.299 position:50% align:center
Yes, a tragedy.

00:18:11.383 --> 00:18:13.802 position:50% align:center
[ALL MIGHT sighs]
Listen, Endeavor.

00:18:13.885 --> 00:18:16.471 position:50% align:center
I understand the situation
you've been placed in

00:18:16.554 --> 00:18:18.890 position:50% align:center
and what's being said about you.

00:18:18.973 --> 00:18:20.600 position:50% align:center
There are many who
can't help but dwell

00:18:20.684 --> 00:18:22.477 position:50% align:center
on our differences.

00:18:22.560 --> 00:18:23.853 position:50% align:center
[BUSINESSMAN 62A] It's not
that I don't like Endeavor,

00:18:23.937 --> 00:18:25.855 position:50% align:center
I just can't help but
compare him to All Might.

00:18:25.939 --> 00:18:27.190 position:50% align:center
And, ya know,
that's kind of a lot

00:18:27.273 --> 00:18:29.359 position:50% align:center
for any hero to
live up to, right?

00:18:29.442 --> 00:18:30.485 position:50% align:center
[TRAINEE 79AA]
All Might!

00:18:30.568 --> 00:18:31.861 position:50% align:center
They came to watch us?

00:18:31.945 --> 00:18:33.071 position:50% align:center
So cool!

00:18:33.154 --> 00:18:34.364 position:50% align:center
Whoa, is that Endeavor?

00:18:34.447 --> 00:18:37.242 position:50% align:center
