[PRESENT MIC] What is this,
a character introduction page?

00:19:53.985 --> 00:19:55.403 position:50% align:center
Come on!

00:19:55.487 --> 00:19:56.571 position:50% align:center
[ALL]
So Boring.

00:19:56.654 --> 00:19:58.573 position:50% align:center
[PRESENT MIC]
Total fail!

00:19:58.656 --> 00:19:59.449 position:50% align:center
Sorry.

00:19:59.532 --> 00:20:02.494 position:50% align:center
That was a nice try, Todoroki!

00:20:02.577 --> 00:20:04.245 position:50% align:center
I guess we have no choice.

00:20:04.329 --> 00:20:06.414 position:50% align:center
[CAMIE]
Hey. You three have been yelling

00:20:06.498 --> 00:20:08.875 position:50% align:center
and running after them this
whole time, but, I dunno.

00:20:08.958 --> 00:20:10.877 position:50% align:center
Wouldn't it be faster if we,
like, just showed them

00:20:10.960 --> 00:20:12.420 position:50% align:center
how cool all our Quirks are?

00:20:12.504 --> 00:20:14.673 position:50% align:center
I was just about
to suggest that!

00:20:14.756 --> 00:20:16.925 position:50% align:center
Whoa, that's a
coincidence, huh?

00:20:17.008 --> 00:20:18.677 position:50% align:center
We have a lot of work to do.

00:20:18.760 --> 00:20:20.387 position:50% align:center
And plenty of these
snot-nosed twerps

00:20:20.470 --> 00:20:22.931 position:50% align:center
seem to think it's fun
to cause us trouble.

00:20:23.014 --> 00:20:24.432 position:50% align:center
We can't just try
to gain their trust

00:20:24.516 --> 00:20:25.892 position:50% align:center
and think that's enough.

00:20:25.975 --> 00:20:29.270 position:50% align:center
We gotta go all in with a
demonstration of our skills.

00:20:29.354 --> 00:20:31.314 position:50% align:center
[YOARASHI]
I see. Got it!

00:20:31.398 --> 00:20:33.400 position:50% align:center
They're planning something.

00:20:34.734 --> 00:20:37.112 position:50% align:center
[KID LEADER] No matter what
they try, it won't work,

00:20:37.195 --> 00:20:39.781 position:50% align:center
because we know the truth.

00:20:39.864 --> 00:20:41.491 position:50% align:center
Our mommies and daddies

00:20:41.574 --> 00:20:43.993 position:50% align:center
and everyone on TV,
they're all wondering

00:20:44.077 --> 00:20:46.079 position:50% align:center
if the age of heroes is over.

00:20:46.162 --> 00:20:48.623 position:50% align:center
[gasps] Careful.
Don't hurt them!

00:20:48.707 --> 00:20:52.252 position:50% align:center
Ha. You guys aren't
foolin' anybody.

00:20:52.335 --> 00:20:53.336 position:50% align:center
We're better than you,

00:20:53.420 --> 00:20:55.422 position:50% align:center
and we'll take you
down to prove it.

00:20:55.505 --> 00:21:01.386 position:50% align:center
Oh? Then bring it on.
Let's have a proper fight.

00:21:01.469 --> 00:21:03.763 position:50% align:center
In the end, all
you Neanderthals

00:21:03.847 --> 00:21:06.516 position:50% align:center
can do is resort
to useless violence.

00:21:06.599 --> 00:21:09.519 position:50% align:center
Of course, that won't work.

00:21:09.602 --> 00:21:10.979 position:50% align:center
[PRESENT MIC] Why are they
having so much trouble

00:21:11.062 --> 00:21:12.814 position:50% align:center
against grade schoolers?

00:21:12.897 --> 00:21:13.982 position:50% align:center
Stooping to their level

00:21:14.065 --> 00:21:16.109 position:50% align:center
would be the epitome
of folly, my peers!

00:21:16.192 --> 00:21:17.360 position:50% align:center
Who is this guy?

00:21:17.444 --> 00:21:19.195 position:50% align:center
It is apparent that you
have not recognized

00:21:19.279 --> 00:21:21.239 position:50% align:center
the superiority of
Shiketsu High.

00:21:21.322 --> 00:21:23.575 position:50% align:center
In order for this commentary
to reflect the truth,

00:21:23.658 --> 00:21:25.410 position:50% align:center
I have decided to assist you.

00:21:25.493 --> 00:21:26.661 position:50% align:center
Say what?

00:21:26.745 --> 00:21:28.705 position:50% align:center
As Present Mic should
already have deduced,

00:21:28.788 --> 00:21:30.623 position:50% align:center
if my peers fight seriously,

00:21:30.707 --> 00:21:33.376 position:50% align:center
the children will be
left beaten, ashamed.

00:21:33.460 --> 00:21:35.795 position:50% align:center
On the other hand,
if they use their discretion

00:21:35.879 --> 00:21:38.214 position:50% align:center
and let the children shine,
then it will only

00:21:38.298 --> 00:21:41.676 position:50% align:center
make the delinquents
even more brazen.

00:21:41.760 --> 00:21:44.304 position:50% align:center
Abandoning discourse
will result in failure!

00:21:44.387 --> 00:21:45.638 position:50% align:center
Hold on!

00:21:45.722 --> 00:21:48.141 position:50% align:center
I don't think you all know
how dangerous this is.

00:21:48.224 --> 00:21:50.018 position:50% align:center
Those children are
strong and believe

00:21:50.101 --> 00:21:53.772 position:50% align:center
wholeheartedly that their Quirks
surpass those of the heroes.

00:21:53.855 --> 00:21:56.566 position:50% align:center
They won't hold back
against your trainees!

00:23:29.325 --> 00:23:30.577 position:50% align:center
[IZUKU]
Here's the preview!

00:23:30.660 --> 00:23:32.454 position:50% align:center
The children of Masegaki
Elementary School

00:23:32.537 --> 00:23:33.997 position:50% align:center
don't have a lot
of faith in heroes

00:23:34.080 --> 00:23:36.499 position:50% align:center
and they believe they can defeat
those in the training class.

00:23:36.583 --> 00:23:37.959 position:50% align:center
That's why they've picked
a fight with Kacchan,

00:23:38.043 --> 00:23:39.753 position:50% align:center
Todoroki, and the others.

00:23:39.836 --> 00:23:41.713 position:50% align:center
If my peers use their
Quirks in the wrong ways,

00:23:41.796 --> 00:23:44.090 position:50% align:center
they won't be able to win
the hearts of these children.

00:23:44.174 --> 00:23:45.508 position:50% align:center
I know my classmates are worthy

00:23:45.592 --> 00:23:47.844 position:50% align:center
of becoming pro heroes,
but can they demonstrate

00:23:47.927 --> 00:23:49.387 position:50% align:center
that to everyone watching?

00:23:49.471 --> 00:23:52.098 position:50% align:center
Next time: "Relief for
License Trainees."

00:23:52.182 --> 00:23:55.393 position:50% align:center
Also, Aoyama is acting even
more eccentric than usual!

